Preheat your oven to 200°C and boil a large #saucepan{} of water over high heat. Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a #frying pan{} on medium-high heat. Season the @skin-on British chicken breasts{2} with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Once the oil is hot, lay in the chicken breasts skin-side down. Fry until the skin is golden, ~{5-6%minutes}, then turn and cook for ~{1%minute} on the other side.

> For the crispiest skin, don't be tempted to move the chicken.

> Wash your hands after handling chicken and its packaging.

While the chicken cooks, trim the @carrots{3} (no need to peel), quarter lengthways and then chop into finger-length batons. Pop the carrots onto a large #baking tray{} and add a drizzle of @oil{}. Sprinkle over the @sugar{1} and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Toss to coat, then arrange in a single layer.

Transfer the chicken to another baking tray (skin-side up). Roast the chicken on the top shelf of your oven and the carrots on the middle shelf, until the carrots are tender and the chicken cooked, ~{20-25%minutes}. Halfway through, add the @garlic cloves{2}(no need to peel) to the carrot tray to cook for ~{10%minutes}.

> The chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Meanwhile, chop the @potatoes{450} into 2cm chunks (no need to peel), and pop them into your pan of boiling water with @salt{1/2%tsp}. Simmer until tender, ~{15-20%minutes}.

> The potatoes are cooked when you can easily slip a knife through them.

Once cooked, drain in a #colander{} and pop them back in their pan. Cover with a #lid{} to keep warm. Meanwhile, thinly slice the @closed cup mushrooms{150}. Halve, peel and thinly slice the @echalion shallot{1}.

Put the frying pan used for the chicken back on medium-high heat. Add a drizzle of @oil{}, the mushrooms, @British smoked bacon lardons{90} and a pinch of @salt{} and @pepper{}. Stir-fry until the mushrooms are golden, ~{4-5%minutes}. Add the shallot and fry until softened, ~{3-4%minutes}. Pour in the @water{125}, stir in the @red wine stock paste{28} and bring to the boil. Lower the heat and simmer until the sauce has reduced by half, ~{4-5%minutes}. Remove from the heat.

> Cook lardons thoroughly.

When the chicken is cooked, transfer it to a #chopping board{} to rest for a couple of mins. Carefully, squeeze the garlic out of its skin and add it to the potato along with a knob of @butter{knob} and a splash of @?milk{a splash}. Add @salt{} and @pepper{} to taste and mash until smooth with a #potato masher{}. Slice the chicken, serve with the mash and carrots. Spoon over the sauce. Enjoy!

> If you've decided to add bacon lardons to your meal, add them to the pan with the mushrooms. Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw meat. Cook lardons thoroughly.